    "description": "Cortical bone modulus (10–20 GPa), UHMWPE block modulus (±15%), and screw-block contact friction coefficient (0.1–0.4) were varied in a one-at-a-time study across the 11-specimen ensemble. Construct stiffness QoI showed peak sensitivity to cortical modulus (±8% response range) while yield force was most sensitive to friction coefficient (±5%); force at 40 mm displacement varied less than 3% across all parameter perturbations, confirming model robustness within the COU envelope."
  },
  "hasContextOfUse": {
